<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Learn DSA</title>
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/style.css' />
    <%- include('../../partials/head') %>
  </head>
  <body>

    <div class="d-flex">
      <%- include('../../partials/sidebar') %>

      <main class="flex-fill p-4">
        <div class="text-center">
          <h3>Binary Search Trees (BST)</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="slide active">
          <div class="slide-content markdown">
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Binary Search Tree (BST) - Introduction

            A **Binary Search Tree (BST)** is a special type of binary tree with an ordering property:

            - Each node has at most **two children**
            - Left child contains **smaller values**
            - Right child contains **larger values**

            ####Left < Root < Right####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              8-->3;
              8-->10;
              3-->1;
              3-->6;
              10-->14;
            /mermaid
            </script>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="slide">
          <div class="slide-content markdown">
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # BST Property

            For every node in a BST:

            - All values in the **left subtree** are smaller
            - All values in the **right subtree** are greater
            - This rule applies **recursively**

            ####∀ node: left < node < right####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              5-->2;
              5-->7;
              2-->1;
              2-->3;
              7-->6;
              7-->8;
            /mermaid
            </script>
          </div> 
        </div> 
        <div class="slide"> 
          <div class="slide-content markdown"> 
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Searching in a BST

            Searching is efficient due to ordering:

            1. Start at the root
            2. Compare value
            3. Go left or right

            ####Time Complexity: O(h)####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              8-->3;
              8-->10;
              3-->1;
              3-->6;
              6-->4;
              6-->7;
            /mermaid
            </script>
          </div> 
        </div>

        <div class="slide"> 
          <div class="slide-content markdown"> 
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Insertion in a BST

            To insert a value:

            1. Start at the root
            2. Follow BST rules (left/right)
            3. Insert at the correct leaf position

            ####Maintains BST property####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              8-->3;
              8-->10;
              3-->1;
              3-->6;
              6-->4;
              6-->7;
              10-->14;
            /mermaid
            </script>
          </div> 
        </div>

        <div class="slide"> 
          <div class="slide-content markdown"> 
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # BST Complexity

            Performance depends on tree height:

            - **Best case (balanced):** O(log n)
            - **Worst case (skewed):** O(n)

            ####h ≈ log(n)####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              A-->B;
              B-->C;
              C-->D;
              D-->E;
            /mermaid
            </script>
          </div> 
        </div>

        <!-- CONTROLS --> 
        <div class="nav-controls"> 
          <button class="btn btn-outline-dark me-2" id="prev">← Prev</button> 
          <button class="btn btn-outline-dark" id="next">Next →</button> 
        </div> 
        <div class="progress-container"> 
          <div class="progress-bar" id="progress"></div> 
        </div> 
        <div class="slide-counter"> 
          <span id="current">1</span>/<span id="total">1</span> 
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
  <script src="/javascripts/render-slides.js"></script>
</html>
